🏔 Heap / Priority Queue

This section covers problems solved using Heap (Priority Queue), focusing on efficiently retrieving minimum/maximum elements and solving top-k queries.

---

📌 Overview

A Heap is a specialized data structure that allows fast access to the smallest or largest element.
It is widely used in problems involving ranking, streaming data, and optimization.

---

🧠 Key Concepts

- Min Heap / Max Heap
- Top K elements
- Streaming data
- Custom comparator usage

---

📘 Problems

- 215 - Kth Largest Element in Array → Min Heap
- 347 - Top K Frequent Elements → Heap + HashMap
- 703 - Kth Largest in Stream → Streaming heap
- 973 - K Closest Points → Max Heap

---

⏱ Complexity

Operation| Time
Insert| O(log n)
Remove| O(log n)
Peek| O(1)

